%I A394338 #8 Mar 24 2026 20:29:26
%S A394338 1,1,20,971,107688,22774522
%N A394338 Number of labeled posemigroups on n elements.
%C A394338 A posemigroup (partially ordered semigroup) is a triple (S, *, <=) where (S, <=) is a partial order, (S, *) is a semigroup (associative binary operation), and * is monotone with respect to <=: for all a, b, x in S, if a <= b then a*x <= b*x and x*a <= x*b.
%e A394338 a(0) = 0 for n = 0, the unique posemigroup is the empty structure which vacuously satisfies all axioms. For each n, the discrete (equality) partial order is compatible with every semigroup, so a(n) >= A027851(n).
%Y A394338 Cf. A001035, A027851, A394339.
%K A394338 nonn,hard,more
